  I have thought about this, and unless you feel extremely negative about these guidelines, here are some things to consider with recruiting.<br>
  Get to know them. - I don't want to have people joining this guild that at least one person does not know.  That is why I would like to instate the concept of vouching for a new recruit.  They must be sponsored and then the sponsor will petition either Ndyira or myself about the applicant.   <br>
  I know that any officer can invite, but I think it best if you contact Ndyira or I first.  I like Ndyira's idea about getting together as officers when we have multiple applications to join, so its not just N's or I's job to say aye or nay to the new member.  <br>
  If you know the person in RL and want to invite, feel free, but please, all I ask is that you tell either N or I about it.  I don't want to have an explosion of new members.  I think that is a discouraging thing when you log on and don't see anyone you recognize in the /who Benevolent.  <br>
  Lets try this system, and see how it works.  If you think of anything you'd like to add to this, please post it.  I don't think there is anything too unreasonable to these suggestions.  It may be some work, but nothing worthwhile was ever easy.  Oh, if you'd rather just post your name, lvl and class to this thread feel free... I'll check it often.  <br>
<br>
Thanks for your help in this matter. <p>Mathusis Furyblade
